Johannesburg - The former chief operations officer at Bosasa, Angelo Agrizzi, appeared at the Zondo commission for a second week and continued with jaw-dropping testimony. He continued to implicate various individuals in the wide-scale corruption that took place at Bosasa involving various government officials. The corruption focused largely on ensuring Bosasa obtained government tenders worth millions of rands. Those implicated by Agrizzi include:   Agrizzi is expected to continue with his testimony on Monday. Politics Hub